      ⍝ ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
      ⍝ MARPLE Demo 3: Namespaces and Standard Library
      ⍝ ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════
      ⍝ ── Qualified names: call system library directly ──
      $::str::upper 'hello world'
HELLO WORLD
      $::str::lower 'MARPLE'
marple
      $::str::trim '   padded   '
padded
      ⍝ ── Import for convenience ──
      #import $::str::upper
      #import $::str::trim
      upper 'imported and working'
IMPORTED AND WORKING
      trim '  no more padding  '
no more padding
      ⍝ ── Import with alias ──
      #import $::str::lower as lc
      lc 'SHOUTY'
shouty
      ⍝ ── File I/O: read a data file ──
      #import $::io::nread
      raw ← nread 'examples/data.txt'
      ⍝ Show shape — it's a character vector
      ⍴ raw
44
      ⍝ ── The i-beam operator: call Python directly ──
      ⍝ This is what the stdlib wrappers use internally
      up ← ⌶'marple.stdlib.str_impl.upper'
      up 'direct i-beam call'
DIRECT I-BEAM CALL
      ⍝ ── List available functions in the str namespace ──
      ⍝ (This would be done in the REPL with )fns $::str)
